From aa6ce04abf38d603953a956318d81482276ab7b1 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: picoclaw-ci <ci@picoclaw.dev>
Date: Wed, 18 Mar 2026 13:04:48 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] fix(tools): propagate tool registry to subagents via Clone
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Fix critical bug where subagents cannot use any tools. SubagentManager
was initialized with an empty ToolRegistry and SetTools() was never
called after the multi-agent refactor, so all subagent tool invocations
returned "tool not found".

Add ToolRegistry.Clone() to create an independent snapshot of the parent
agent's tool registry, then call subagentManager.SetTools(agent.Tools.Clone())
in registerSharedTools() — giving subagents access to file, exec, web,
and other tools while preventing recursive subagent spawning.

Also fix pre-existing build error in cron_test.go where SubscribeOutbound()
was called but doesn't exist on MessageBus (replaced with OutboundChan()).

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
